div1.p:
I live in Church-street in the strand; I lost some pewter pots about a fortnight ago; seven pint pots, three quart pots, and an half gallon one; I found them again the next morning; I missed them out of a court, they were getting in, in the afternoon;
William Stevenson
brought them next morning.

I am an apprentice to Mr. Penly, No. 69, Cable-street;
Mary Chitty
pledged the sheets on the 7th of December one pair of sheets; she had fetched the sheets and blankets out often; I have the sheets here. (Deposed to by the prosecutor.)

I can swear that to be my master's property; this piece had been a bar to a window;
John Hawkins
brought it back the 17th, at night almost seven o'clock; that chimney bar is the only piece I can swear to, we had had it in the house about a fortnight before he had had it.
